Set on 14,951m² of rolling lawns, this mansion on one of Gauteng’s swankiest equestrian estates boasts American colonial style architecture with unique features including a piano lounge, mahogany bar and designer kitchen. Accommodation comprises five bedrooms, six bathrooms as well as a separate guest studio. The property also has four stables, a tack/feed room, fenced paddocks and lunging arena. The V&A Waterfront’s newly developed Silo district, which is home to among others the Museum of Contemporary Art Africa (Zeitz Mocaa), is fast becoming one of Cape Town’s most sought-after residential addresses. Record prices of between R100,000/m² and R200,000/m² have been achieved for apartments at No 3 Silo, which offers luxury living within walking distance of the city centre and the Waterfront.